<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Estimation">Estimation</h2>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</sp=
an><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBlood_alcohol_co=
ntent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: Estimation"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Direct_measurement">Direct =
measurement</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsectio=
n-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3D=
Blood_alcohol_content&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit sect=
ion: Direct measurement"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection=
-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Blood samples for BAC analysis are typically obtained by taking a venous=
 blood sample from the arm. A variety of methods exist for determining bloo=
d-alcohol concentration in a blood sample.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Dubowski_23-0=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcoho=
l_content#cite_note-Dubowski-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Forensic laboratories typicall=
y use <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Headspace_gas_chromatography=
_for_dissolved_gas_measurement" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Headspace ga=
s chromatography for dissolved gas measurement">headspace-gas chromatograph=
y</a> combined with mass spectrometry or flame ionization detection,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-24" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-24"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>23<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> as this method is accura=
te and efficient.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Dubowski_23-1" class=3D"reference"><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-Dubow=
ski-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>]</span></a></sup> Hospitals typically use <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Enzyme_multiplied_immunoassay_technique" title=3D"Enzyme multipli=
ed immunoassay technique">enzyme multiplied immunoassay</a>, which measures=
 the co-enzyme <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NADH" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"NADH">NADH</a>. This method is more subject to error but =
may be performed rapidly in parallel with other blood sample measurements.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-25" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-25"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In Germany, BAC is determined by measuring the serum level and then =
converting to whole blood by dividing by the factor 1.236. This calculation=
 underestimates BAC by 4% to 10% compared to other methods.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-26" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_=
alcohol_content#cite_note-26"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>25<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"By_breathalyzer">By breatha=
lyzer</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBlood_=
alcohol_content&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: B=
y breathalyzer"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breathalyzer" title=
=3D"Breathalyzer">Breathalyzer</a></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Breathalyser_%27pint%27_glass_-_2023-03-27_-_=
Andy_Mabbett.jpg" class=3D"mw-file-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.=
wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/Breathalyser_%27pint%27_glass_-_=
2023-03-27_-_Andy_Mabbett.jpg/250px-Breathalyser_%27pint%27_glass_-_2023-03=
-27_-_Andy_Mabbett.jpg" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"190" height=3D"253" cla=
ss=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"2400" data-file-height=3D"3200"><=
/a><figcaption>Joke "Breathalyser 'pint<span style=3D"padding-right:.15em;"=
>'</span>" beer glass, about 2 inches tall, dating from around the time of =
the introduction of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breathalyzer" =
title=3D"Breathalyzer">breathalyzers</a> in the United Kingdom, in 1967</fi=
gcaption></figure>
<p>The amount of alcohol on the breath can be measured, without requiring d=
rawing blood, by blowing into a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Br=
eathalyzer" title=3D"Breathalyzer">breathalyzer</a>, resulting in a breath =
alcohol content (BrAC). The BrAC specifically correlates with the concentra=
tion of alcohol in arterial blood, satisfying the equation <span class=3D"t=
exhtml">BAC<sub>arterial</sub> =3D BrAC =C3=97 2251 =C2=B1 46</span>. Its c=
orrelation with the standard BAC found by drawing venous blood is less stro=
ng.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-27" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-27"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>26<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Jurisdictions =
vary in the statutory conversion factor from BrAC to BAC, from 2000 to 2400=
. Many factors may affect the accuracy of a breathalyzer test,<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-28" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blo=
od_alcohol_content#cite_note-28"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>27<sp=
an class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> but they are the most common m=
ethod for measuring alcohol concentrations in most jurisdictions.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-29" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-29"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>28=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"By_intake">By intake</h3><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBlood_alcohol_cont=
ent&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D6" title=3D"Edit section: By intake"><s=
pan>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></=
div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacology_of_etha=
nol#Modeling" title=3D"Pharmacology of ethanol">Pharmacology of ethanol =C2=
=A7&nbsp;Modeling</a></div>
<p>Blood alcohol content can be quickly estimated by a model developed by S=
wedish professor Erik Widmark in the 1920s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Ed_30-0" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_con=
tent#cite_note-Ed-30"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>29<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The model corresponds to a <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacokinetic" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"=
Pharmacokinetic">pharmacokinetic</a> single-compartment model with instanta=
neous absorption and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zero-order_ki=
netics" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Zero-order kinetics">zero-order kine=
tics</a> for elimination. The model is most accurate when used to estimate =
BAC a few hours after drinking a single dose of alcohol in a fasted state, =
and can be within 20% <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coefficient_=
of_variation" title=3D"Coefficient of variation">CV</a> of the true value.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-31" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[=
</span>30<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-32" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alc=
ohol_content#cite_note-32"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>31<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It is not at all realistic for the a=
bsorption phase, and is not accurate for BAC levels below 0.2 g/L (alcohol =
is not eliminated as quickly as predicted) and consumption with food (overe=
stimating the peak BAC and time to return to zero).<sup id=3D"cite_ref-33" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_=
content#cite_note-33"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>32<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-Jones2011_5-10" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_conte=
nt#cite_note-Jones2011-5"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The equation varies depending on the u=
nits and approximations used, but in its simplest form is given by:<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-:3_34-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-:3-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle EBAC=3D{\frac {A}{V_{d}}}-\beta \times T}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mi>B</mi>
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>C</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mi>A</mi>
            <msub>
              <mi>V</mi>
              <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                <mi>d</mi>
              </mrow>
            </msub>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=88=92<!-- =E2=88=92 --></mo>
        <mi>=CE=B2<!-- =CE=B2 --></mi>
        <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
        <mi>T</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle EBAC=3D{\frac=
 {A}{V_{d}}}-\beta \times T}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/c8cdc1a6ecd6ab58b7cf7fc40aaf803b04909d20" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
