l-align: -2.338ex; width:22.08ex; height:5.843ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle EB=
AC=3D{\frac {A}{V_{d}}}-\beta \times T}"></span>
</p><p>where:
</p>
<ul><li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">EBAC</spa=
n> is the estimated blood alcohol concentration (in g/L)</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span> is t=
he mass of alcohol consumed (g).</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">T</span> is t=
he amount of time during which alcohol was present in the blood (usually ti=
me since consumption began), in hours.</li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B2</span>=
 is the rate at which alcohol is <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
limination_(pharmacology)" title=3D"Elimination (pharmacology)">eliminated<=
/a>, averaging around 0.15 g/L/hr.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-35" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note=
-35"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup></li>
<li><span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">V<sub>d</sub>=
</span> is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Volume_of_distribut=
ion" title=3D"Volume of distribution">volume of distribution</a> (L); typic=
ally body weight (kg) multiplied by 0.71 L/kg for men and 0.58 L/kg for wom=
en<sup id=3D"cite_ref-MaskellVd_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-MaskellVd-36"><span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a>=
</sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-MaskellMass_37-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-MaskellMass-3=
7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</s=
pan></a></sup> although estimation using TBW is more accurate.<sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-:3_34-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Blood_alcohol_content#cite_note-:3-34"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup></li></ul>
<p>A standard drink, defined by the WHO as 10 grams of pure alcohol,<sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-WHO_AUDIT_EN_38-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
